\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Discussion based on Mitchell's MWA paper
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What fraction of the full FoV can be imaged without the sources suffering
 significant flux distortions? (Does this make sense? why should sources
 far away from the phase center have flux distortions?)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Keywords
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Fundamental aspects to address in this paper:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Ideal set of parameters for imaging from the AARTFAAC.
 Do these need to change as a function of observing time?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How to maximize point source sensitivity of the AARTFAAC?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Interpolation scheme for lower computational load.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Process of generating stacked images from spectral cubes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Appropriate deconvolution process.
 Iterative or analytic?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Image noise analysis as a function of observing time, and as a function
 of field of view in a snapshot.
 What fraction of the field of view can be reliably imaged?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Approach to source finding, temporal window, or remap to geocentric coordinates?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Effect of Galactic plane and Solar modelling on image dynamic range.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Temporal stacking at different cadences for increased sensitivities: What
 limits do we have?
\end_layout

\end_inset


